      "### Does baking soda actually remove car odors?",
      "Yes — for surface and absorbed odors it works well. Sprinkle plain baking soda over dry carpet and upholstery, leave it overnight, and vacuum it out completely. It absorbs odor molecules rather than masking them, and it leaves no residue or competing fragrance. It won't fix an active moisture source, though, so dry the cabin and stop the leak first.",
      "### How often should I replace my cabin air filter to avoid musty smells?",
      "Most manufacturers recommend every 12,000–15,000 miles, but if you've had a mildew issue, replace it as part of the cleanup regardless of mileage — a contaminated filter recirculates the smell on every fan setting. After that, a fresh filter every year or so keeps a hidden odor reservoir from building back up."
